You may be able to postpone or stop your home being repossessed. 

[Community Legal Advice](http://legaladviserfinder.justice.gov.uk/AdviserSearch.do "Community Legal Advice"){:rel="external"} offers free, confidential and independent legal advice. It can also help you find a solicitor.  

$C
**Community Legal Advice**  
0845 345 4 345  
Monday to Friday, 9am to 8pm  
Saturday, 9am to 12:30pm
$C

You can also get free advice from:

+ [Citizens Advice](http://www.citizensadvice.org.uk/index/getadvice "Citizens Advice"){:rel="external"} 
+ [Consumer Credit Counselling Service](http://www.cccs.co.uk/ "Consumer Credit Counselling Service"){:rel="external"} 
+ [National Debtline](http://www.nationaldebtline.co.uk/ "National Debtline"){:rel="external"} 
+ [Payplan](http://www.payplan.com/ "Payplan"){:rel="external"} 
+ [Shelter](http://www.shelter.org.uk/ "Payplan"){:rel="external"} 
+ your [local council](http://local.direct.gov.uk/LDGRedirect/Start.do?mode=1 "Find your local council"){:rel="external"}
